# Before/After Slider

## How the wipe works

- **After** sits on the bottom layer, filling the frame (`absolute inset-0`, `fill`, `object-contain`)
- **Before** sits on top in the **same full frame**, clipped with `clip-path` by handle position
- The clip divides the **frame**, not a small image box — both layers must be `inset-0`

```tsx
<div className="relative overflow-hidden" style={{ height: 920 }}>
  <div className="absolute inset-0">
    <Image src={afterSrc} fill className="object-contain" unoptimized />
  </div>
  <div className="absolute inset-0" style={{ clipPath }}>
    <Image src={beforeSrc} fill className="object-contain" unoptimized />
  </div>
</div>
```

## Avoid

- Positioning images in small calculated boxes inside the frame — the clipped before region is mostly empty, so after bleeds through everywhere (looks like after is "not in the slider")
- Per-image pixel layout with shared scale for "alignment" — breaks wipe when images don't fill the clip region
- `h-auto w-auto` on Next `Image` (ignores computed box)

## Image sizing

- Fixed frame: `width: 100%`, `height: 920px`, `overflow: hidden`
- `object-contain` on both — full image visible, no crop
- `unoptimized` + cache-bust query strings when swapping assets in `projects.ts`
